# Copy this to .env.local and fill in your values
# Also add these as Environment Variables in the Vercel dashboard

# ── Facebook Graph API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used for Fidesz and Magyar Tisza Párt Facebook pages.
# One token covers both pages.
#
# HOW TO GET IT (one-time, ~10 minutes):
#
# 1. Go to https://developers.facebook.com/apps and create a new app
#    (type: "Business" or "Consumer", doesn't matter)
#
# 2. Go to https://developers.facebook.com/tools/explorer
#    - Select your app from the top-right dropdown
#    - Click "Generate Access Token"
#    - Add these permissions: pages_read_engagement, pages_show_list
#    - Click "Generate Access Token" and approve
#
# 3. You now have a SHORT-LIVED token (~1 hour). To make it permanent:
#    - Go to https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/accesstoken
#    - Paste your token and click "Debug"
#    - Click "Extend Access Token" at the bottom
#    - Copy the long-lived token (~60 days)
#
# 4. To make it truly never-expire (Page token):
#    - In Graph Explorer, run: GET /me/accounts
#    - Find the page (FideszHU or magyartisza) in the response
#    - Copy its "access_token" value — this Page token never expires
#    - Use THAT token here
#
FACEBOOK_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_facebook_page_access_token_here

# ── Twitter/X ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT NEEDED — Twitter feeds use rss.app RSS feeds, no API key required.
# The feed URLs are hardcoded in lib/config.js.
